The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Sept 16: The rate of inflation appears to have ended the downward march as it rose marginally to 3.16 per cent in the week-ended September 3, even as the impact of petrol and diesel price rise is yet to be felt on the general price level. 

 Mumbai, Sept 16: Bombay High Court today gave its nod to a committee formed by Reliance Industries Ltd on the demerger of the group companies for settlement between siblings Mukesh and Anil Ambani.

 New Delhi, Sept 16: The government has set up a high-level independent committee to inquire into the fire accident at the Mumbai High field in July. The committee will be chaired by former petroleum secretary T.N.R. Rao. 

 Mumbai, Sept. 16: Procter amp; Gamble Hygiene and Health Care Ltd will sell off its detergent manufacturing business to Procter amp; Gamble Home Products Ltd. The shareholders have approved the move through postal ballot.

 New Delhi, Sept. 16: The government will meet the target for fiscal and revenue deficits for this financial year despite ?minor deviations? on monthly basis and increase in expenditure on development programmes.




